<img class=" size-medium wp-image-42224 alignleft lazyload" src="http://www.ngrguardiannews.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/cibn-300x225.jpg" alt="cibn" width="300" height="225" />THE Chartered Institute of Bankers of Nigeria Lagos State Branch is set to hold its yearly Bankers’ Nite at the Federal Palace Hotel, Victoria Island,Lagos on August 13. According to the organisers, the event will be focusing on theme “Rebuilding the value system: The strategic imperative for Nigerian economic development”. The forum, which is expected to provide unique opportunity for the exchange of ideas on contemporary economic and banking issues, will also open opportunity for Bankers to interact with top people who have break-even in the banking sector. The Guest speaker is Prof. Akin Oyebode, a re-known professor of Law while the keynote address will be delivered by Frank Aigbogun, the publisher of Business Day, and other prominent people in attendance such as Oba of Lagos, Riliwanu Akiolu, the royal father for the day while the Lagos State Governor, Akinwumi Ambode will be the Guest of honour. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .